:INFO
Writing and Self-Publishing a Solo RPG Game
Writing and self-publishing a solo RPG (a journaling RPG or oracle-driven game). Covers game design fundamentals, writing prompts and oracles, PDF layout, and distribution on itch.io and DriveThruRPG.

:COUNTER.half
2 to 6 USD
Common price range for solo RPG PDFs on itch.io
|
:COUNTER.half
8 to 24 Pages
Typical length for a standalone solo RPG product

:PATH
Game Design
Choose your oracle system: a tarot deck, standard playing cards, a d6 table, or a custom prompt deck. Design around the oracle. Write the framing premise: who the player is, what they are doing, and why it matters.

:PATH
Writing the Game
Write in second person. Keep rules minimal and focused on enabling play. Include at least one random table. Write safety tools into the text. Edit for clarity above all else.

:PATH
Distribution and Pricing
Publish on itch.io first. Submit to the Itch.io Solo RPG collection. Consider DriveThruRPG for a wider audience once the game has reviews. Set a price of 2 to 5 USD with a pay-what-you-want floor.

:CHECKLIST
Pre-Release Checklist
[ ] Game playable from start to finish alone
[ ] Rulebook readable without explanation
[ ] PDF exported at 300 DPI with embedded fonts
[ ] itch.io page complete with cover image
[ ] Safety tools included in the text
[ ] Playtesters acknowledged

:NOTE
The solo RPG market on itch.io is active and supportive. The Alone Together and Hinchcliffe Award communities provide visibility for new releases. A strong cover image and a one-paragraph pitch are your most important marketing assets.

